Procam Slam 24-25

latestPosts.caption:
Procam Slam 24-25! What a journey it has been! Tougher journey although begins now! To one AVERAGE runner to another - “You got this!” Did I start this slam with thinking of doing “PB”? No. But did I have the urge everytime to do a bit better than the last? Yes.
That urge and motivation comes within right? No one can give that to you! The consistency is what I knew would just take me ahead!
Ofcourse doing this slam I knew wasn’t going to be easy with planning and travelling alone but luckily made some friends along😇
Managing all this while going through extreme anxious moments wasn’t easy at all either😇
Truly grateful! 
Shall be on DND mode okay😜

latestPosts.caption:
Official course time 4.30❤️ 1 hr PB from last year!
Yesterday Mumbai was no less than a shola! Marathon is a distance you need to respect because it will humble you and how! Had to switch to Plan B execution after few kms realising the heat will be unbearable and I would not be able to sustain it otherwise!! 
This year has been such a roller coaster with April being completely off running due to the lower back injury! But I took it as a challenge instead!! Decided to become a strong runner instead because hey we want to do this for more years na?! 

Thanks to @fitpage for taking care of all the plans and nutrition! Thanks to @vishal_marathon @siddhi_r211 and @coach_yatish !
Thanks to @corehab_physio Pooja for taking care of last minute problems and the bigger problems the earlier year 😅😅
PS - 9th in my age category! 

Do you believe in having a Plan B?

Procam Slam 24-25 now got me closure!! 🧿 7th overall in the Delhi- Bangalore cycle! Little did I know that I could be in the top 10 of the procam slam leaderboard! Honestly a long way to go yet but I am going to enjoy this soak it all in because this didn’t come easy! Had days when I cried by myself.. Worklife , Switching jobs in between, Love , everything taking a toll! People around me were “settling down” and me? I was running crazy🤪 So finally I can say cheers to this journey and what’s to come! 🥂 @procamintl

Showing up for yourself, especially when it gets difficult!! Currently the weather is making it worse!
I honestly come from a different mindset when it comes to running..
Have said it before that I don’t want to be the fastest person, I want to run for as long as I can!! Speed? Pace? Time? Doesn’t matter. Yes I want to see myself growing but what’s important is to soak in all if it! Rest of all it is a plus!
I just have been showing up and having fun! 😇🧿 So kids moral of the story - HAVE FUN!🤪
